The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 26: Ashok Leyland will raise $150 million through global depository receipts or other securities in the international markets. The shareholders, at the AGM held on August 1, have authorised the board to issue global depository receipts, foreign currency convertible notes or other convertible securities to raise up to $150 million, subject to necessary approvals, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 New Delhi, Aug. 26: Power Grid Corporation of India has synchronised northern, eastern, northeastern and western electricity grids as a step towards a pan-India national transmission grid. The grid network has a total generation capacity of 88,000 mw from 250 power plants.

 Mumbai, Aug. 26: Tech Mahindra, which had fixed its initial public offer price at Rs 365 per share earlier this month after a public issue that was oversubscribed by more than 71 times, will list its shares on the Bombay Stock Exchange and the National Stock Exchange on August 28.




